After 18 years, I finally got my dream car. 1992 Nissan 240sx Coupe S13. I cannot express how thankful I am to all those supporting me, and to the lovely companies I’ve partnered with. Thank you to @petrv.png for not only taking some amazing pictures and giving me this opportunity 🥰

The 240sx is now running and driving! Big thank you to @petrv.png @protatojae @kvswrx and @_matthewseven for helping me achieve a dream I never thought would be possible. 

I’ve done suspension, brakes, transmission swap, @gktech_official short shifter, gauge cluster, fan and fan clutch, and more. Before I got the shop, I had never really even changed my own oil. Believe me when I say that anything is possible! And thanks to TJ I’m even learning how to drive manual on the street! I cannot wait to see what the rest of this year brings. After 9 years of planning were finally doing it!

I have to also say a big thank you to Hugo and Marc at @advancedsimracing for believing in my dream and helping me get into sim drifting. You guys are the best! 👊🏽 

Big ups to the boys and girls at @shadowrealmgg — without you I couldn’t do any of this. I’m proud to say I’m the leader of the best team in the world. I cannot wait to conquer the drift scene with you guys! Thank you for believing in me 🥰

new seat and wheel thx to @425motorsports u da man Judson :))

happy to be workin with y’all this year and onwards 👊🏽 

seat didn’t end up fitting in the car without modification, so ended up putting in Petra’s old S14 seat. the new driving position is cash though, and the steering wheel makes me feel like I’m right in my sim. Super comfy. 

Next steps for the s13 are to find some front turn signals and it’ll be safe and road legal! I am beyond stoked to finally own an s chassis and bless with friends like @_matthewseven and @petrv.png  to help me get the car on the road and driving.

Big ups to @02bluehawk @sartin_logic_ and @sara.choi for helping me figure out how to make this shizz work. And of course shout outs to my @shadowrealmgg boys and girls. I could not do it without you! Y’all kick ass 👊🏽 

📸: @petrv.png

I’m so incredibly thankful to have the best friends and team that I have. @shadowrealmgg goes hard IRL and online. Thank you so much for one of the most fun and relaxing days I’ve had in a while. I needed it.

I’m completely in love with this sn95 mustang. It needs a lot, but I’m honestly convinced she’s a good ship that’ll turn into a straight ripper with some hard work and tuning. 

I’m planning on attending @spirit.peaks.raceway ‘s May 6th Open Drift event as my first event ever. Since last February when I dedicated my life to drifting, I’ve gone from learning how to drive stick and drift on sim, to getting a real shop with my friends, to building a drift car and now a tow rig, to planning my first IRL drift event.

I honestly can’t explain how incredibly excited I am. I’m nervous that I’m going to mess up, but I have the utmost faith that I will succeed and eventually make it as a professional driver and content creator. 

I’ve been so incredibly blessed with the countless opportunities and people that have stepped into my life and helped me along my journey. I cannot even begin to thank you enough. I’d run out of room if I tried to tag you all, but I know you know what’s good. I want to also say thank you so much to my sponsors for allowing me to take content creation and drifting this seriously as well.

Finally, I want to thank my family, Mercy, and the big man upstairs for watching over me and being there when I fall. I know my faith will continue to guide me onwards. 

This is just the beginning of a lifelong journey, but I’ve never felt more accomplished and confident in my decisions. If you don’t know me already, I invite you to join me on this journey to the top!

An 8 year dream in the making. I first met @_matthewseven in 2014/15 through a mutual friend and learned about drifting. I went to the track multiple times with him and wanted to skid more than anything. Me being me though, I spent the next 7 years trying to figure out how to drift for the rest of my life. How to integrate my skills and passion as a content creator with drifting and automotive. I couldn’t figure out the finance part either. How to build a business around drifting in a way that only I could. I paywalled myself over and over and gatek*pt my self from drifting. I said oh next year I’ll save a little more so I can take a year off and pursue drifting. I need a 2nd car, a truck, a trailer, a shop, mechanical knowledge, tools, and a parking spot for all of it. 

Last year I finally decided to just full send it. I sought sponsorship with @advancedsimracing and started learning how to drive stick and eventually drift on #AssettoCorsa. I decided to do an entire year of sim drifting before I ventured in to the real world. My team, shadowrealm, now hosts the SRDL which is the biggest sim drift comp in North America, as well as the #1 grassroots competition aimed at getting new drivers into drifting and gaining experience in competition. We are also partnered with ESDA and VOSAN which is a dream come true. I am the leader of @shadowrealmgg , the best team in the world. 

The hesitant at first I spent a good amount of time on the skid pad to get the feel for driving stick on track as I have only been driving stick for the last few weeks. Then with some minor coaxing and major coaching from @_matthewseven and Regan, I eventually moved from the skid pad to the big boy track. Unfortunately, I don’t have any phone footage from that, but I managed to link 3 turns!!

I WILL become the face of drifting, I WILL compete in grassroots, I WILL gain my pro license, and I WILL earn my spot on @formulad

I haven’t been back to the Philippines since I was a younger. I used to hate the Philippines. For personal reasons mostly — I was extraordinarily stupid as a kid; close minded would be an apt descriptor. I saw the world through a very one dimensional lens. Black and white, no shades of grey. One was either right or wrong — there was always a correct answer. It’s how we were taught in school. Full of self righteousness and pride and youthful ignorance; I never thought I’d change my mind.

But as all kids do, I grew up. I realized there may be truths to life, but never universal or even constant. Everyone experiences reality in a shifting spectrum. What may be truth for one can be a wash of lies for others. Reality is in essence a framework or construct of our souls to provide guidance and meaning for our existence.

With fresh eyes and an open heart I’ve decided to experience life here not as the ignorant kid so many years ago but as an adult with overwhelming childlike joy and curiosity. I truly hope I can set out on this new adventure and experience why my people are so proud of our home and document it. I’m unsure if I’ll ever be “Filipino”, but I’m dead set on finding out.

PERFECT COMBO GET!

After 4 weeks of aim/ergo research and a big shoutout to Optimum Tech on YouTube, I’ve finally obtained what I believe to be the best mouse and mousepad combo. The @finalmouse ULX, with 4k polling, 1600 dpi and around .21-.24 in game @valorant sensitivity feels flawlessly smooth and accurate. Paired with the @skypadgg 3 XL in white it’s stunning. I’ve never been an aesthetics geek but I can definitely appreciate it. Now to wait for my @wootingkb 60HE with all the trimmings and it’ll be a thanksgiving to remember hahaha 👨🏽‍🍳
Tearing down the studio and moving the sim rig to the living room. Also made a cozy lil couch gaming area :) feels really good to check things off the list and be streaming/content creating again 💪🏽
